The paper proposes a method for truth discovery, which involves resolving conflicts and finding the truth from multiple-source statements. This is a common problem in areas such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), databases (cs.DB), computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of memory network based models is also a common technique in these areas, further supporting the likelihood of these sub-categories.
